We’ve had good luck using YOLOv5 on a Jetson Nano and the TensortRTx library. Last season we could recognize cones and cubes at 60hz. We used RoboFlow for annotating the data set and were able to merge our data with that of other teams to get a dataset of more than 1000 images. Not sure if YOLOv8 would offer any improvements. The new Jetson Orin-Nano ought to offer some significant performance improvements beyond our original Jetson.

Hey, glad you used Roboflow for your datasets! I’m one of the co-founders & ran across this post on a Google search. Wanted to chime in with a few things:

  1. Is this dataset public on Roboflow? If so, could you link me to it? In 2022 we had an intern highlight a bunch of FIRST Datasets for others to use. Would love to feature yours (and other good ones). And if anyone would like an internship helping curate datasets, models, and content/tutorials for FRC teams we’d love to talk.
  2. Roboflow also does model training & deployment; you can use inference (our open source package) to run models trained in the platform (or shared on Universe) & YOLOv5, YOLOv8, and other models on your Jetson.
  3. We sponsor a bunch of teams with increased Roboflow image & GPU credits. All we generally ask is that you help spread the word (especially to any team mentors that work in industry since selling things to companies is how we give things away to students and hobbyists); this can be with a link back to your Roboflow dataset in your Github repo or a guest blog post or something like that. (Apply at roboflow .com/contribute)

Using search terms “frc 2023 cone cube” in Roboflow turned up a number of other data sets. Let me know if you’re looking for anything else.

Nice! I’m glad our search is turning some of those up. It’s hard to know which ones of those are good/valuable (or well labeled) without diving in deeper.

I marked yours as featured on this page! You may want to edit the README on the project’s Sharing page on your account to give context & take credit (or link back to your team/github).

If others have found useful datasets (especially with trained models) let me know & I can highlight them too.
